    "shortDescription": "Tarantulas are the largest spiders in the world, and despite their intimidating appearance, most species are slow-moving and relatively calm. Their real defense weapon isn't their fangs — it's the tiny barbed hairs on their abdomen that they flick at threats using their back legs, causing intense irritation. Fun fact: Some tarantulas live for over thirty years, making them one of the longest-lived invertebrates you could keep as a pet."
